2) RDD with simulated model¶

We generate the simulated data points. We define $Y_a$ as the average nonemployment duration at age $a$ in months.

In [9]:
@time let
    freq = 1/12 # 1 for yearly, 1/12 for monthly, 1/365 for daily
age_grid0 = (46:freq:54) *12 #daily: (46:(1/365):54) *12 or monthly: (46:(1/12):54) *12
Y = [expectedD(a,V,austria) for a in age_grid0]
    
table = zeros(7)

#explaining variables
TREAT = age_grid0 .>= austria.A
consta = ones(size(age_grid0))
age1 = collect(age_grid0)
age2 = age1 .^2
age3 = age1 .^3
age1_spl = (age1 .- austria.A) .* TREAT 
age2_spl = (age1 .- austria.A).^2 .* TREAT 
age3_spl = (age1 .- austria.A).^3 .* TREAT 

## no trend
X = hcat(TREAT, consta)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[1] = beta[1] 

## linear spline
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[2] = beta[1]

## cubic spline
X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl, age2, age2_spl, age3, age3_spl)
beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
table[3] = beta[1]

## with different bandwidths
for (i,band) in enumerate([2.,1.,0.5,0.2] *12)
    myindexes = austria.A - band .<= age_grid0 .<= austria.A + band
    age_grid = age_grid0[myindexes]
    newY = Y[myindexes]
    
    #explaining variables
    TREAT = age_grid .>= austria.A
    consta = ones(size(age_grid))
    age1 = collect(age_grid)
    age1_spl = (age1 .- austria.A) .* TREAT 

    ## linear spline
    X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )   
    beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * newY)
    table[3+i] = beta[1] 
end        

## RDD estimates from the data on the left
display(hcat([14.6, 14.8, 11.15, 0,0,0,0]*12/52 ,table))
end

println("The standard errors are: ", [1.07, 1.93, 3.47]*12/52)

3) Discussion¶

The role of $m$ and $q$

In [11]:
function whatbias(;m=austria.m, q0=austria.q0, qa=austria.qa, Aret=austria.Aret, χ=austria.χ)
    freq = 1/12
    age_grid = (48:freq:52)*12. 
    newC = update_Country2(α=austria.α, m=m, q0=q0, qa=qa, Aret=Aret, χ=χ)
    newV =  find_Surplus(newC)

    ## RDD estimate 
    Y = [expectedD(a,newV,newC) for a in age_grid]
    TREAT = [a>=austria.A for a in age_grid]
    consta = ones(size(age_grid))
    age1 = collect(age_grid)
    age1_spl = (age1 .- austria.A) .* TREAT 
    X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )
    beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
    RDDestimate = beta[1] 

    ## LATE
    expD_without = expectedD_without(austria.A, newV, newC)
    expD_with = expectedD_with(austria.A, newV, newC)
    LATE =  (expD_with-expD_without)
    return (RDDestimate, LATE)
end


function whatbias2(;m=austria.m, q0=austria.q0, qa=austria.qa, Aret=austria.Aret, χ=austria.χ)
    freq = 1/12
    age_grid = (48:freq:52)*12. 
    newC = update_Country2(α=austria.α, m=m, q0=q0, qa=qa, Aret=Aret, χ=χ)
    newV =  find_Surplus(newC)

    ## RDD estimate 
    Y = [expectedD(a,newV,newC) for a in age_grid]
    TREAT = [a>=austria.A for a in age_grid]
    consta = ones(size(age_grid))
    age1 = collect(age_grid)
    age1_spl = (age1 .- austria.A) .* TREAT 
    X = hcat(TREAT, consta, age1, age1_spl )
    beta = inv(X' * X) * (X' * Y)
    RDDestimate = beta[1] 

    ## LATE
    expD_without = expectedD_without(austria.A, newV, newC)
    expD_with = expectedD_with(austria.A, newV, newC)
    LATE =  (expD_with-expD_without)
        
    ## RDD estimand
    expD_bef = expectedD(austria.A-0.001, newV, newC)
    expD_aft = expectedD(austria.A, newV, newC)
    RDDand =  (expD_aft-expD_bef)
    
    return (RDDestimate, RDDand, LATE)
end

In [ ]:
Ndata = 50
scale = 0.1
data3D = zeros(Ndata^2,5)
i0 = 0
selecX = []
selecY = []
mdec_vec = vcat(range(-1,stop=0,length=Integer(Ndata/2)),range(0.001,stop=1,length=Integer(Ndata/2)))
qdec_vec = vcat(range(-1,stop=0,length=Integer(Ndata/2)),range(0.001,stop=1,length=Integer(Ndata/2)))
i=0
@time for mdec in mdec_vec, qdec in qdec_vec
    global i +=1
   # logscale = 2
    newm = austria.m*(1+mdec*scale) #austria.m*logscale^mdec
    newq0 = austria.q0*(1+qdec*scale) #austria.q0*logscale^qdec
    (RDDestimate, LATE) = whatbias(m=newm, q0=newq0)

    data3D[i,:] = [mdec, qdec, RDDestimate, LATE , RDDestimate-LATE] 
    if (mdec == 0) & (newq0 <= austria.q0 )
        push!(selecY, i)
    end
    if (qdec == 0) & (newm >= austria.m )
        push!(selecX, i)
    end
    if (mdec == 0) & (qdec == 0)
        global i0 = i
    end
end

## table of bias
makerow(text, RDD, LATE) = [text round(RDD,digits=2) round(LATE,digits=2) round((RDD-LATE)/(abs(LATE))*100,digits=1)]
function makerow(text::String, wb2)
    (RDD, RDDand, LATE) = wb2
    println("The estimate, estimand and LATE $text are $RDD, $RDDand and $LATE")
    return makerow(text, RDD, LATE) 
end

mytab = DataFrame(makerow("in the calibrated model", whatbias2()), :auto)
push!(mytab, makerow("without trend", whatbias2(qa=0.)))
push!(mytab, makerow("without horizon", whatbias2(Aret=200. *12)))

for aa in [60, 55]
    push!(mytab, makerow("with horizon at $aa", whatbias2(Aret=aa *12.)))
end
